Richard J. Daly  Chairman of the Board, CEO, President and Interim Principal Financial & Accounting Officer, Neuralstem, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships56$1,759,723As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Richard J. Daly, also known as Rich, has been the Chief Executive Officer and President at Neuralstem, Inc. since February 15, 2016 and its Principal Financial and Accounting Officer since April 28, 2017. Mr. Daly served as the Interim Chief Commercial Officer of Catalyst Pharmaceuticals, Inc. from May 28, 2015 to August 17, 2015. He served as Managing Director of Ravine Rock Partners, LLC. He served as the President of US Diabetes Alliance at AstraZeneca Pharmaceuticals ... LP from 2013 to 2014. He has over 20 years of commercial pharmaceutical experience working in positions of progressive responsibility in sales, marketing and operations. He began his career in the Sales and Marketing organization for the Takeda-Abbott joint venture (JV) partnership “TAP,” where he progressed to senior leadership roles. From 2011 to 2013, Mr. Daly was a Founding Partner and Board Member of SagePath Partners LLC. He co-founded SagePath Partners in 2011. He served as Vice President of Marketing and Commercial Strategy of Tap Pharmaceutical Products, Inc. since February 13, 2006. He was responsible for leading the overall marketing strategy and initiatives for TAP's current and future brands - including Prevacid(R) (lansoprazole) and Lupron Depot(R) (leuprolide acetate for depot suspension), febuxostat, managed markets marketing and sales, new product planning - as well as its business insights/analytics function and marketing operations. He managed all elements of commercial strategic and tactical implementation; refocused the commercial structure and strategy on stabilizing the business in highly competitive markets; and on improving short- and long-term profitability. He served as Senior Vice President of Integration where he delivered the project ahead of schedule with significant financial synergies. He began his pharmaceutical career at TAP in 1991 and served in several leadership roles, including Senior Marketing Director. In his career, he served in the sales organizations at Merrell-Dow Pharmaceuticals (now part of Sanofi) and TAP Pharmaceuticals (formerly a division of Abbott Labs) in sales, marketing, operations and senior leadership positions at TAP and Takeda. He served as Senior Vice President of Marketing for Takeda Pharmaceuticals North America, located in Lincolnshire, Ill. During his recent tenure at Takeda Pharmaceuticals he served as Executive Vice President with P&L responsibility for businesses across the U.S., Canada and Central/South America. He was a Founding Member of the senior leadership team that built Takeda's commercial infrastructure and successfully launched the diabetes drug Actos(R) (pioglitazone HCl). He serves on the board of Andean Health & Development. He has been the Chairman of the Board at Neuralstem, Inc. since June 13, 2016. He has been a Director at Neuralstem, Inc. since February 15, 2016 and Catalyst Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since February 2015. He has been an Independent Director of Synergy Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since July 1, 2015. Mr. Daly holds a BS in Microbiology from the University of Notre Dame in South Bend, Ind. and an MBA from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University in Evanston, Ill.Read Full Background




